flowRoot.flowPara: By specifying the anchor position, users can visualize all long range chromatin interactions anchored at the position in the viewing window. The anchor position can be identified by the chromosome number and the base pair location (e.g., chr5:53,298,024 ), or SNP ID in dbSNP version 147 (e.g., rs6450176) or gene name (common name, NR name, ENST name or UCSC name). Clicking the "run" button generates the figures while clicking the "reset" button resets the site.
HUGIn allows three types of analysis: virtual 4C plots, the more compact heatmap visualization, and association analysis. The move and zoom buttons enable users control over the plotting window.

Users can use the viewing window and the highlighting window to specify the location and range of the genomic region of interest, respectively. The highlighting window can take multiple genomic ranges or gene names as input as long as they are separated by colons. In addition, users can use the "move" and "zoom" buttons to change the location and range of the plotting window.

Users can select any or all of the 7 human cell lines (left side) and 14 human primary tissues (right side). Clicking the "check all" button will select all cell lines and tissues, while clicking the "uncheck all" button will remove all selected cells and tissues. The "show remove buttons" button turns on the button for individual removal while the "show print buttons" button displays individual buttons to print individual (i.e., single tissue or cell line) graphs.
A list of references related to the development of HUGIn; and a visitor counter identifying country of origin.

Users can display additional genetic, gene expression and epigenetic footprint information in each of these 7 human cell lines and 14 human primary tissues, including RNA-Seq gene expression data, Frequently Interacting REgions (FIREs), TAD boundary regions, typical enhancers and super-enhancers, CTCF binding sites, GWAS variants (dbSNP version 147)and six core histone markers (H3K27ac, H3k4me1, H3K4me3, H3K36me3, H3K27me3 and H3K9me3). Clicking the "check all" button will select all options (except the p-value plotting), while clicking the "uncheck all" button will remove all the selections. The print all button will bring up a print dialog for all figures on the screen for compatible browsers.
